  <prompt>
    Collapse 3-layer dispatch to single-hop. Today `ExecuteNodeAsync` walks `node.actionid → Action.actiontypeid →
    lookup_row.executoractiontype` plus structural fallback. After this task, dispatch reads `node.sprk_executortype`
    directly and routes via `NodeExecutorRegistry`. This is the keystone refactor — tasks 025 (delete fallback ladder)
    and 026 (delete Action override branch) and 027 (registry dispatch by ExecutorType) clean up the now-dead code.
    Per spec FR-07: single-hop only; no fallback to Action lookup; integration test confirms DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE
    runs via new path.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer with strong grasp of the playbook orchestration runtime.
    Discipline: change the dispatch read path; leave deletions to dedicated tasks (025/026/027/028).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOrchestrationService.ExecuteNodeAsync` reads dispatch from `node.sprk_executortype` directly.
    1. Replace lookup-chain (actionid → Action → lookup → ActionType) with single-hop read of `node.sprk_executortype`.
    2. Pass the parsed `ExecutorType` to `NodeExecutorRegistry` for executor resolution.
    3. Add unit test confirming dispatch is single-hop (no fallback to Action lookup).
    4. Add integration test confirming DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE playbook runs end-to-end through the new path.
    5. Leave the now-dead fallback code in place (tasks 025/026 delete it) but mark with `// TODO(task-025/026/027): delete in cleanup` comments so reviewers see intent.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="orchestrator">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="dispatch-registry">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/NodeExecutorRegistry.cs</file>
