  <context>
    <background>
      Today's dispatch is the artifact of three R-series projects (R3.1 + R4 + Insights Engine r2 Wave B) each adding
      a layer without removing the prior. The result: walk `actionid` → Action → lookup → INT column, with structural
      fallback inferring dispatch when the column is null. R7 collapses this to a single read.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="022" status="must-be-complete">`ActionType` renamed to `ExecutorType`; orchestrator can pass `ExecutorType` to registry.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 025 deletes the structural fallback ladder (~150 LOC) made dead by this change.</item>
      <item>Task 026 deletes the Action override branch (lines 1241-1278) made dead by this change.</item>
      <item>Task 027 updates NodeExecutorRegistry to dispatch by ExecutorType.</item>
      <item>Task 028 simplifies AnalysisActionService read path (no ActionType from Action lookup).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in BFF; modifies orchestrator hot path; ADR-010+013+029+038 applicable; quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read CLAUDE.md + spec FR-07 + plan.md Wave 2 + bff-extensions.md + docs/architecture/ai-architecture-playbook-runtime.md.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read PlaybookOrchestrationService.ExecuteNodeAsync">
      Locate the current dispatch logic. Identify the 3-layer lookup chain. Identify the structural fallback ladder + Action override branch (lines ~863-1079 + 1241-1278 per plan.md). Capture the exact line ranges in a sub-note for tasks 025 + 026.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read NodeExecutorRegistry">
      Confirm registry's resolution signature — should be able to accept an `ExecutorType` and return an `INodeExecutor`. If signature change needed, document for task 027.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement single-hop dispatch">
      In `ExecuteNodeAsync`, add the new path: parse `node.sprk_executortype` (Dataverse Choice value INT) into `ExecutorType` enum; look up executor via `NodeExecutorRegistry`; invoke `ExecuteAsync`.
      Wrap the old fallback code in a clear "// DEAD CODE — task 025/026/027 delete in cleanup" comment block; do NOT delete in this task (cleanup tasks own the diff).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Handle null sprk_executortype">
      Per FR-19, all 94 existing nodes will be backfilled (Wave 5). Until then, a null value should THROW with a clear error message ("Node {id} has null sprk_executortype — backfill required per FR-19"). Do NOT silently fall back to the old path; that defeats the refactor.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Add unit test (no fallback)">
      In `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationServiceTests.cs` (or sibling), add: when node has `sprk_executortype = AiAnalysis`, executor resolved via registry directly; Action lookup table is NEVER queried. Mock the Dataverse client; assert no Action-lookup call.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Add integration test (DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE)">
      Stub or wire integration test for the DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE playbook (depends on task 015 backfill of those Actions; if blocked, scaffold the test with [Skip] and note the dependency).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + run tests">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must be green. New unit test green. Existing tests still green (fallback code still present, untouched).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read ExecuteNodeAsync — confirm single-hop is the primary path; old code is marked for deletion.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the diff — focus on the dispatch logic + null handling.
      Run `/adr-check` against ADR-010 + ADR-013 + ADR-029 + ADR-038 + bff-extensions.md.
      Fix any findings.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 024 complete; advance current-task.md.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      `feat(bff/r7): single-hop dispatch in PlaybookOrchestrationService (Wave 2 task 024, FR-07)`.
      Body: cite FR-07; mention follow-on tasks 025/026/027 delete the dead-code blocks.
    </step>
  </steps>

